Chicken Piccata Meatballs
  --Natalie Mortimer

Meatballs:
1 1/2 lb ground chicken
1/2 c panko breadcrumbs
1/2 c freshly grated Parmesan cheese
2 cloves garlic, minced
1/4 c finely chopped fresh flat leaf parsley, plus more for garnish
2 tbsp capers, finely chopped
1 medium shallot, finely chopped
1 large egg, lightly beaten
1 tsp kosher salt
1/2 tsp freshly ground black pepper
1 tbsp evoo

In a large bowl, combine the ground chicken, panko, Parmesan, garlic, parsley, capers, shallot, egg, salt, and pepper. Mix well, then with wet hands, form golf ball-size meatballs (~2 tbsp each) and place on a plate. You should have 16-18 meatballs. Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Once the oil is glistening, add the meatballs in a single layer. Cook until browned on all sides, 6-8 minu. Transfer to a separate plate. 

Sauce:
6 tbsp unsalted butter, divided
4 cloves garlic, minced
1 shallot, finely chopped
1 c chicken stock
1/2 c dry white wine
1/4 c freshly squeezed lemon juice, (from 2 lemons)
2 tbsp capers, drained
1/4 c chopped parsley
lemon slices, for garnish

In the same skillet, add 2 tbsp of the butter. Once the butter is melted, add the shallot and cook, stirring, until softened, ~3 min. Add the garlic and cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~1 min more. Pour in the wine and chicken stock, scraping up any browned bits from the bottom, and simmer until reduced by about half, 4-5 min. Stir in the remaining 4 tbsp butter, lemon juice, and capers into the sauce. Return the meatballs to the skillet. Cover and cook until the meatballs are cooked through and the internal temperature reads 165F on an instant-read thermometer, ~8-10 min. Serve over mashed potatoes, buttered cooked pasta or cooked orzo (if using), sprinkled with chopped parsley and garnished with lemon slices. 

  




